Weapons are used to fight various Mobs or in PvP.

There are two main weapon classes:

  • Swords - This includes any melee / magical weapon.
  • Bows - all of which require some kind of ammunition in the inventory/Quiver.

The type of weapon you choose can change what Enchantments and Reforging can be used on it.

Weapons

  • Swords
  • Bows
  • Ability-Damage Weapons

[edit tab] [view/purge tab]

Swords0

A Sword is any melee Weapon which has a Sword tag, regardless of its shape and ability. They can be enchanted and reforged to modify their Stats/effectiveness.

Sword Upgrades

Sword upgrades are upgrades that can be applied to any sword in the game. Sword upgrades include things such as Enchantments, Hot Potato Books, and reforges. Expensive enchantments like Sharpness VI and Ender Slayer VI should only be used on later-game weapons or higher, such as the Midas Sword, and Aspect of the Dragons, due to their cost.

It is recommended to max out top-tier end-game swords such as the Midas Sword, Aspect of the Dragons, when used with a high level Ender Dragon Pet, and Emerald Blade, when used with a purse of at least 250 million Coins, as there aren't any better swords to obtain, so the only way to increase weapon damage is through upgrades.

Like with the Ender Dragon Pet, some pets can upgrade a weapons damage output. For example, the Blaze Pet doubles all hot potato book effects. The effect can be sextupled with Mushroom Armor and quadrupled with Ender Armor.

Vanilla Swords

This item is part of vanilla Minecraft. More information can be found at:
Minecraft Wiki: Weapons

All vanilla Minecraft swords exist in SkyBlock, although SkyBlock alternatives are almost always better. The wooden version is used in various Minion recipes.

Icon Material Rarity Damage
Wooden Common 20
Golden Common 20
Stone Common 25
Iron Common 30
Diamond Uncommon 35
A "Thick Wooden Sword" can be created by applying a Wood Singularity on a normal Wooden Sword which would give it an additional +100 Strength and upgrade its rarity from Common to Uncommon, although due to its cost and better weapons to apply it on, this is not recommended. A better use would be on a Tactician's Sword or Scorpion Foil.

This page contains in-game content which has been recently or is being updated.

Bows are ranged Weapons that fire arrows/special ammo from your inventory (or Quiver) which is consumed on use.

Bow Upgrades

These upgrades can be applied to any bow, increasing its stats.

  • Reforges
  • Enchantments
  • Hot Potato Books

Ability-Damage Weapons0

Ability Damage is the damage dealt through any given item or weapon when using its ability.

Increasing Base Ability Damage

Having a high intelligence can increase the ability damage of items in the game.

The Sheep Pet can increase ability damage from 0 to 50 depending on the level. The ability goes up in terms of 0.5 per level.

The Loving reforge obtained from the Red Scarf Reforge Stone can increase your ability damage by 5% when applied to chestplates.

Formula

Ability Damage=Base Ability Damage(1+(Intelligence100)Ability Scaling)

See table below for ability scaling

Notes

  • Some abilities deal Magic Damage that ignore the target's Armor stat.
  • Dungeon Mobs takes less Magic Damage.
    • Melee Dungeon Mobs has 10% Magic Resistance.
    • Ranged Dungeon Mobs has 30% Magic Resistance.
    • Chaos Guardian has 80% Magic Resistance.
    • Magic-type Dungeon Mobs has 90% Magic Resistance.
    • Selective Dungeon bosses and mini-bosses have some Magic Resistance.
